\subsection{Faraday effect} \label{sec:Faraday}
A traveling optical field addresses the hybrid mode via \textit{Faraday effect} or \textit{spin-Raman} effect~\cite{SB1966}. The Faraday effect can be understood phenomenologically as that the polarization of the linearly polarized light rotates due to the circular birefringence of the transparent material. Any material showing circular birefringence possesses non-zero vector polarizability and exhibits the \textit{vector light shift} in the ground-state Zeeman manifold~\cite{HM1967,Julsgaard2003,HSP2010}, which leads to the Faraday effect.

